msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Copy of the Qurʼān from the first sūrah through sūrat al-Anʻām verse 165.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 92 paginated leaves : 213 x 170 (165 x 110) mm bound to 215 x 175 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern pagination added in pencil, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī in dark brown ink; pointed and vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated polychrome marginal medallions showing text divisions; sūrah titles in red and green; green and yellow points throughout the text; vocalizations in red, readings in blue.

decoNote.n: Inside back cover flap open to show design

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind stamped central diamond with blind tooled border and frame; plain paper doublure cut into a zigzag pattern along the outside edges.

origin.p: The item is undated and unsigned, but was probably copied in North Africa in the late 19th century; machine made paper.

history.provenance: Gift of Dr. Joseph Levitsky to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on library bookplate, inside front cover).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate, inside front cover).
